snippet: Exports of live animals could reach a million a year and benefit the domestic market by raising beef prices.
abstract: Australia is close to signing agreement to ship live cattle to China, opening up significant market for producers, who say exports could grow to one million animals a year.
lead_paragraph: Exports of live animals could reach a million a year and benefit the domestic market by raising beef prices.

headline.main: Australia Nears Deal to Sell Cattle to China
headline.print_headline: Australia Nears Deal to Sell Cattle to China
